## 🚀 Next.js Architecture: Full-Stack React Framework

Next.js is a React framework built by Vercel that extends React with built-in server-side rendering, static generation, API routes, file-based routing, and production optimizations. It bridges the gap between React frontend and a Node.js backend.

---

## 1️⃣ Why Next.js Over Create React App?

| Feature | Create React App | Next.js |
|---|---|---|
| Rendering | Client-side only | SSR, SSG, ISR, CSR |
| Routing | Manual (React Router) | File-based (automatic) |
| API routes | Separate server needed | Built-in `app/api/` |
| SEO | Poor (SPA) | Excellent (pre-rendered) |
| Performance | Good | Excellent (image, font, script optimization) |
| Deployment | Any static host | Vercel (or any Node host) |

---

## 2️⃣ File-Based Routing (App Router)

The folder structure determines the routes — no route configuration needed:

```
app/
  page.tsx                → /
  about/
    page.tsx              → /about
  courses/
    page.tsx              → /courses
    [slug]/
      page.tsx            → /courses/react-mastery
  dashboard/
    layout.tsx            → Shared layout for /dashboard/*
    page.tsx              → /dashboard
    settings/
      page.tsx            → /dashboard/settings
  api/
    users/
      route.ts            → API endpoint: GET/POST /api/users
      [id]/
        route.ts          → GET/PUT/DELETE /api/users/:id
  not-found.tsx           → Custom 404 page
  error.tsx               → Error boundary
  loading.tsx             → Loading UI
```

---

## 3️⃣ Rendering Strategies

**Server Components** (default in App Router) — render on the server, never shipped as JS:

```typescript
// app/courses/page.tsx — Server Component (no 'use client')
async function CoursesPage() {
  // Data fetching happens on the SERVER — DB access, secrets safe!
  const courses = await db.query("SELECT * FROM courses")
  return <CourseGrid courses={courses} />
}
```

**Client Components** — run in browser, can use hooks:

```typescript
'use client'  // Opt-in to client-side rendering

function LikeButton({ postId }) {
  const [liked, setLiked] = useState(false)  // Hooks only work in Client Components
  return <button onClick={() => setLiked(true)}>Like</button>
}
```

---

## 4️⃣ SSR, SSG, ISR, and CSR

| Rendering | When HTML is Generated | Best For |
|---|---|---|
| **SSG** (Static Site Generation) | At build time | Marketing pages, blogs |
| **ISR** (Incremental Static Regeneration) | Build time + revalidated periodically | Product pages, frequently updated static |
| **SSR** (Server-Side Rendering) | On every request | User-specific pages, real-time data |
| **CSR** (Client-Side Rendering) | In browser | Interactive dashboards |

```typescript
// SSG — cached permanently (default for static pages)
export const dynamic = 'force-static'

// ISR — regenerate every 60 seconds
export const revalidate = 60

// SSR — server renders on every request
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'
// or: use unstable_noStore() inside the component
```

---

## 5️⃣ API Routes (Route Handlers)

```typescript
// app/api/users/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const searchParams = request.nextUrl.searchParams
  const page = searchParams.get('page') || '1'

  const users = await db.find().skip((+page - 1) * 10).limit(10)
  return NextResponse.json({ users })
}

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  const body = await request.json()
  const user = await db.create(body)
  return NextResponse.json(user, { status: 201 })
}

// app/api/users/[id]/route.ts
export async function GET(request: NextRequest, { params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const user = await db.findById(params.id)
  if (!user) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Not found' }, { status: 404 })
  return NextResponse.json(user)
}
```

---

## 6️⃣ Layouts

Layouts wrap pages and persist across navigations (no re-render):

```typescript
// app/layout.tsx — Root layout (wraps all pages)
export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <Header />
        <main>{children}</main>
        <Footer />
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}

// app/dashboard/layout.tsx — Nested layout for dashboard pages
export default function DashboardLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <div className="dashboard">
      <Sidebar />
      <div className="content">{children}</div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

---

## 7️⃣ Next.js Image Component

```typescript
import Image from 'next/image'

// Optimizes images: WebP conversion, lazy loading, proper sizing
<Image
  src="/hero.jpg"
  alt="Hero image"
  width={1200}
  height={630}
  priority           // Load immediately (above the fold)
  placeholder="blur" // Show blur while loading
/>

// Remote images (add domain to next.config.js)
<Image
  src="https://res.cloudinary.com/..."
  fill
  alt="Profile photo"
  className="object-cover"
/>
```

---

## 8️⃣ Server Actions

Server Actions allow forms to call server functions directly — no API route needed:

```typescript
// app/actions.ts
'use server'

export async function createPost(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get('title') as string
  const content = formData.get('content') as string

  await db.posts.create({ title, content })
  revalidatePath('/posts')  // Refresh cached page
}

// Usage in a Server Component
import { createPost } from './actions'

export default function NewPostPage() {
  return (
    <form action={createPost}>  {/* No event handler needed! */}
      <input name="title" />
      <textarea name="content" />
      <button type="submit">Publish</button>
    </form>
  )
}
```

---

## 9️⃣ Middleware

Middleware runs before every request — use for auth, redirects, A/B testing:

```typescript
// middleware.ts (root of project)
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'
import type { NextRequest } from 'next/server'

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const token = request.cookies.get('token')?.value
  const isProtectedRoute = request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/dashboard')

  if (isProtectedRoute && !token) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', request.url))
  }

  return NextResponse.next()
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/dashboard/:path*', '/api/protected/:path*']
}
```

---

## 🔟 Metadata & SEO

```typescript
// Static metadata
export const metadata = {
  title: 'MERN Bootcamp | Mwenaro Academy',
  description: 'Fullstack engineering bootcamp ...',
  openGraph: {
    title: 'MERN Bootcamp',
    images: ['/og-image.jpg'],
  },
}

// Dynamic metadata (based on data)
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
  const course = await getCourse(params.slug)
  return {
    title: `${course.title} | Mwenaro Academy`,
    description: course.description,
  }
}
```

---

## 💡 Summary

| Concept | Key Point |
|---|---|
| App Router | File → URL mapping automatically |
| Server Components | Default, render on server, no JS shipped |
| Client Components | `'use client'`, can use hooks |
| SSG | Build-time rendering |
| ISR | Build-time + `revalidate` interval |
| SSR | `force-dynamic`, renders per-request |
| API routes | `app/api/route.ts` |
| Layouts | Persistent UI wrapping child pages |
| Middleware | Guard routes before request reaches page |
| Image | `<Image>` — auto-optimize format, size, loading |
| Server Actions | `'use server'` functions called from forms |
